nthropogenic and gravitationnal hazards","Hydrology","Tectonics"],"leaders":["S. Michel (Laboratoire de Géologie","ENS Paris)"],"popup":"fmt-under","width":110},"geometry":{"type":"Polygon","coordinates":[[[31.8760874258152,28.0900869520305],[32.65871767337764,27.966061246031604],[32.7743445397849,27.4501029092911],[34.363042784640975,27.69574167403976],[36.4238394058572,27.3576274980155],[36.648404006947466,28.35425500793752],[37.2776185018302,28.4550796340691],[36.9925441016523,29.88156378227169],[37.23868904047681,30.973965773812523],[38.7750314470572,31.2016839042792],[38.09787329578303,34.700851649960775],[38.2490843042986,35.340190524873876],[39.9795696943692,35.592371364122],[39.1186169363457,39.528714202978],[37.11300725131656,39.2803267277591],[37.1079522537927,39.3029541992994],[36.42404151065596,39.20263468403824],[34.1545714659046,39.5193573308337],[33.2197465523517,34.8942361148249],[35.22504793299303,34.63670500787568],[35.2144091086576,34.58513116716884],[33.2918670063887,34.3086849418805],[33.696425429210635,32.533169038208925],[32.7555044743829,32.6619188769309],[32.513662225686794,31.404651787124802],[31.9093486220907,31.3099485390157],[32.22473557756756,29.90260668124771],[31.8760874258152,28.0900869520305]]]}},{"type":"Feature","properties":{"image":{"src":"/data/images/MAGHREB.png","attribution":"Google Earth Screenshot"},"id":"urn:ogc:def:EOP:CNES::MAGHREB:","uuid":"e3af66f8-e5dc-48bd-8833-61cb27dc8492","link":"https://en.poleterresolide.fr/data-access/catalog/#/metadata/e3af66f8-e5dc-48bd-8833-61cb27dc8492","name":"Maghreb","location":"Maghreb",
"marker":{ "lat": 33.8339199536547, "lng": 0.7343338763908271 },"description":"The main aim of this project is to quantify tectonic deformation across the Maghreb, in the African/Eurasian convergence zone. In particular, it aims to estimate the spatial distribution and temporal evolution of interseismic deformation or deformation associated with recent earthquakes on active faults, from the coast to the Saharan platform. Secondary themes (landslides, coastal subsidence, dune movement in the Sahara, anthropogenic deformation associated with major structures, natural resource extraction, agriculture, etc.) will also be addressed.","theme":["Landlisdes","Tectonics","Hydrology","Hydrocarbon Reservoir Dynamics"],"leaders":["C. Doubre (ITES)"],"popup":"fmt-under","width":110},"geometry":{"type":"Polygon","coordinates":[[[-11.540271192077,32.468893073021],[-10.0935174400771,26.1136060274984],[-7.59044625362264,26.5040423450437],[-7.789786048211599,27.499644801175517],[-5.80005505775587,27.8197592507441],[-5.998878317199276,28.8345192661869],[-3.98682329552808,29.1517878620818],[-4.1019272685958805,29.731401360947572],[-2.7211424498482657,29.94568554145207],[-2.72091376252843,29.9446944932608],[-2.425173688581881,29.991616973056615],[-2.10717996200365,30.0409664619706],[-2.1073934801590966,30.042036367392477],[-0.104188168569822,30.3598673583217],[-0.20414467181887047,30.858122525620864],[1.78998695807073,31.1618830559849],[1.7169419770706051,31.526386295251665],[3.72302302443349,31.8322084409336],[3.597079360172028,32.4569670793188],[5.58824599073073,32.7728286599051],[5.5440867526785365,32.991628115532556],[6.814462512481883,33.17634150494017],[6.878201,32.905281],[8.853485843955534,33.20209014820681],[8.99546797811469,32.6006551215955],[11.6959679955817,33.0041387144138],[10.7832332661967,37.5511637664897],[8.781563550664096,37.27313506156111],[8.75137019775099,37.4238203783134],[6.7526391777663655,37.14064959264853],[6.71387598692983,37.3386187458494],[4.723409359900168,37.057906763126795],[4.72318645321901,37.05901121743],[1.88588866783406,36.65509236723],[1.8859218547464267,36.65495157886576],[-0.105979687952991,36.372798938051],[-0.0712920223302074,36.2265975881916],[-2.0602418059632,35.94205372456],[-1.9893168858641601,35.640061313913186],[-3.1894310425315275,35.463954012914805],[-3.338889,36.212864],[-5.332202754061988,35.92653311612828],[-5.33325196207988,35.9318164709429],[-8.12785506072472,35.5204460143684],[-7.725432874349526,33.7664355731304],[-9.704005,33.471752],[-9.547291672532547,32.773716362736714],[-11.540271192077,32.468893073021]]]}},{"type":"Feature","properties":{"image":{"src":"/data/images/MAKRAN.png","attribution":"Google Earth Screenshot"},"id":"urn:ogc:def:EOP:CNES::MAKRAN:","uuid":"d569dbcc-0a13-4f60-a116-e4c54c1bf205","link":"https://en.poleterresolide.fr/data-access/catalog/#/metadata/d569dbcc-0a13-4f60-a116-e4c54c1bf205","name":"Makran","location":"Makran","description":"The project aims to analyze strain partitioning along the Makran active margin, a convergence zone between Arabia and Eurasia. This region is characterized by major thrust fault systems and laterally variable seismic behavior (large earthquakes in the east, more moderate seismicity in the west). The mode of strain accumulation on active tectonic structures will be analyzed together with the lithospheric structure and geology, in order to better constrain the seismic hazard and geodynamic history of the region.","theme":["Tectonics"],"leaders":["S. Chevrot (GET)","D. Remy (GET)"],"popup":"fmt-under","width":110},"geometry":{"type":"Polygon","coordinates":[[[56.2057693224771,25.8717871414151],[57.82121757464902,25.78606277279627],[58.01785616931966,24.88745685460797],[59.90657010037995,25.208982561779546],[60.64642238818637,25.10300545502334],[61.48976638294062,29.0104814622753],[59.73309569387755,29.28335652477344],[59.60643017577807,29.92307745160581],[57.00633362123747,29.50994792565148],[57.0379684438826,29.36538200817549],[56.835437479544,29.3713172630271],[56.2057693224771,25.8717871414151]]]}},{"type":"Feature","properties":{"image":{"src":"/data/images/TIANSHAN.png","attribution":"Google Earth Screenshot"},"id":"urn:ogc:def:EOP:CNES::TIANSHAN:","uuid":"136a5eab-a672-406e-8876-d5a87fb38acb","link":"https://en.poleterresolide.fr/data-access/catalog/#/metadata/136a5eab-a672-406e-8876-d5a87fb38acb","name":"Tian Shan","location":"Tian Shan","description":"The aim of the project is to analyze deformation across the intracontinental Tianshan mountain range, linked to the India/Asia collision. In particular, the aim is \n(1) to quantify the partitioning of deformation between thrust faults and strike-slip faults, \n(2) to gain a better understanding of the behavior of folds and thrusts during the seismic cycle, in the foothills and at the heart of the range, \nAnd (3) to document regional-scale slope phenomena (landslides, permafrost freeze-thaw deformation, solifluction, etc.), in relation to seismicity and climate change.","theme":["Permafrost","Tectonics","Landslides"],"leaders":["M. Rizza (CEREGE)"],"popup":"fmt-under","width":110},"geometry":{"type":"Polygon","coordinates":[[[69.26,40.1],[71.05648027112079,39.855580915493775],[71.28,39.04],[73.28312349726777,39.316292896174865],[73.37,39],[75.32773083531049,39.26510938394829],[75.34,39.22],[75.64050980392157,39.26027450980392],[76.15,39.19],[76.18959763602449,39.33386360070431],[78.25,39.61],[78.24611587913334,39.62779738964277],[80.24,39.9],[79.40082028244862,43.774107868996566],[79.76,45.05],[79.10710157051534,45.13007244889906],[78.91,46.04],[75.87896040937248,45.6762752491247],[75.98,46.05],[72.69,46.45],[72.49002189901661,45.52679282703909],[69.6,45.17],[70.02042174723856,43.63596112465929],[69.26,40.1]]]}}]}
